        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 2 at 4:26PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 426 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Abilene, or near Coronados Camp, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Abilene, Tye, Buffalo Gap, Coronados Camp, Potosi, View, Caps, Dyess
Afb, Impact, Lake Abilene, Camp Tonkawa, and Kirby Lake.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 273 and 292.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
